GM: NOT A VOW. Ylva doesn't make vows — Ylva makes decisions, and
the decision is the same as the action. She is not heartbroken. She is
not sad. She is a wolf who walked up to the den and found a stranger
in it, and the stranger was polite and reasonable and WRONG, and the
woman who should be there is buried underneath.

This is the seed of YLVA-AS-ANTI-ISMARA. Her pursuit of Davinia was
romantic — heat, curiosity, the desire to crack the ice. It is now
something else: pack-loyalty. The romance isn't gone, but it's been
subsumed into something older and less negotiable. Ismara is an
intruder. Davinia is pack. You get your pack back.

RESOLVE NOTHING. This plants the seed. The pursuit IS the re-anchoring
